<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="J" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Jay" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Jay,</orth> the bird Corvus glandarius: <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.173" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 173</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 3, 10</bibl>. Denoting a loose woman: <cit><quote>we'll teach him to know turtles from --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 44</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>some j. of Italy hath betrayed him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 51</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>